        <h1>
            Issue Tracking
        </h1>

        
        
        <h2>Issue Tracking for WSO2 BAM Product</h2>
        <p>Issues, bugs, improvements and feature requests for the <a href="http://wso2.org/projects/bam">
            WSO2 BAM product</a> should be submitted to the
            following issue tracking system.</p>
        <div class="source">
            <a class="externalLink" href="http://wso2.org/jira/browse/BAM">http://wso2.org/jira/browse/BAM</a>
        </div>
        <h2>Issue Tracking for WSO2 Carbon Platform</h2>
      <p>
        WSO2 BAM is developed on top of the WSO2 Carbon platform. To get an overall
        idea on the issue management of the WSO2 BPS, you might need to have a look at the
        WSO2 Carbon platform's issue tracking as well.
      </p>
        <p>
          Issues, bugs, improvements and feature requests for the <a href="http://wso2.org/projects/carbon">
            WSO2 Carbon platform</a> should be submitted to the following issue tracking system.</p>
        <div class="source">
            <a class="externalLink" href="http://wso2.org/jira/browse/CARBON">http://wso2.org/jira/browse/CARBON</a>
        </div>
      <p> If you are just interested in the BAM component specific issues, have a look at </p>
      <div class="source">
        <a class="externalLink" href="https://wso2.org/jira/browse/CARBON/component/10493">BAM component's core issues</a>
        <br/>
        <a class="externalLink" href="https://wso2.org/jira/browse/CARBON/component/10494">BAM component's UI issues</a>
        <br/>
        <a class="externalLink" href="https://wso2.org/jira/browse/CARBON/component/10495">BAM component's documentation issues</a>
        <br/>
      </div>
      
      <h2>Issue Traking System</h2>
      <p>
        This project uses
        <a class="externalLink" href="http://www.atlassian.com/software/jira">Atlassian Jira</a>, a J2EE-based,
        issue tracking and project management application. You can find more information on how to report an issue 
        form 
        <a class="externalLink" href="http://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/v3.13/introduction.html">
        Atlassian's Jira help pages.</a>
      </p>

